  "name": "Galatians 6:11–18",
  "localizedName": "Galatians 6:11–18",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jews who believed that Jesus is the Messiah didn’t need to obey the Law of Moses. Yet Jewish leaders treated Jews badly if they didn’t obey Jewish laws."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Some Jewish believers in Galatia didn’t want to be "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108054",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "treated badly"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " for following Jesus. So they wanted everyone to think that they still followed all the Jewish laws."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "They also tried to make Gentile believers follow Jewish laws about circumcision. Paul explained that the laws about circumcision didn’t matter anymore. What matters is the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108543",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "new creation"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " that Jesus brought when he died on the cross."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Paul’s body had scars from being treated badly for following Jesus. He was willing to suffer for belonging to Jesus."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
